# Harmony patches

- Each feature exposes a static `{Feature}Patches.Apply(Harmony harmony)` method registered in `FeatureModules.All`.
- Put patch types under `Features/{Feature}/Patches/` as separate types (one file per patched game type); `{Feature}Patches.Apply` uses `HarmonyPatchHelper.GetNamespacePatchTypes`.
- Use `HarmonyPatchHelper.GetNestedPatchTypes` / `GetNamespacePatchTypes` for discovery and `ApplyPatchTypes` for apply + logging.
- Define `private const string Feature = "FeatureName"` matching the config section and log tag.
- Prefer `AccessTools.Method` / `AccessTools.Field` over string literals when the target type is known.
- Static `TargetMethod()` helpers must return a valid `MethodBase` or Harmony will fail silently — log via `HarmonyPatchHelper` audit on failure.
- Do not patch game types without confirming signatures in `deps/decompiled/**/*` (MimesisInspectionTool only as a quick fallback).
- Wrap patch bodies in try/catch; log recoverable failures with `ModLog.Warn(Feature, ...)` — do not swallow silently.
